Edward Wells (1821 – 9 February 1910)
was an English businessman and Conservative Party politician from Wallingford, which was then in Berkshire. He sat in the House of Commons of the United Kingdom from 1872 to 1880.

The Wallingford by-election of 1872 was fought on 9 March 1872.  The byelection was fought due to the Death of the incumbent MP of the Conservative Party, Stanley Vickers.  It was won by the Conservative candidate Edward Wells, who was unopposed.
